During a virtual forum on gender equality, Vice President Kamala Harris emphasized the importance of women's participation in democracy. She highlighted the threats to democracy around the world, such as the rise of strongmen, human rights abuses, and corruption. Harris argued that gender equality is essential to addressing these challenges. She pointed out that democracy is stronger when everyone participates, and weaker when people are left out. She mentioned how women's access to capital, reproductive healthcare, and freedom from violence can contribute to a stronger democracy. Harris made commitments to reinforce institutions in the United States to improve the lives of women both domestically and globally. She addressed young leaders participating in the forum, urging them to use the tools of democracy, fight for freedoms if they don't have them, listen to marginalized voices, and embrace diversity. Harris concluded by emphasizing that democracy and the world are stronger when everyone is included.